The paper deals with interference reduction in downlink cellular networks using MIMO and OFDM technologies, which falls under the category of Information Theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses scheduling and precoding techniques, which are relevant to Networked Systems (cs.NI) and Signal Processing (cs.SI). The use of simulations to evaluate the performance of the proposed scheme suggests that the paper may also be relevant to Multimedia (cs.MM) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories.
